 315:				;
 316:				; *** Console Output ***
 317:				;
 318:				; Translates a character. Call with character in C.
 319:				;
 320:				; Console translation is enabled. Unrecognised sequences are
 321:				; transmitted without modification, so applications can still send VT-100 /
 322:				; ANSI sequences if desired. Translations are:
 323:				; Esc A to Esc [ A - Cursor up
 324:				; Esc B to Esc [ B - Cursor down
 325:				; Esc C to Esc [ C - Cursor right
 326:				; Esc D to Esc [ D - Cursor left
 327:				; Esc H to Esc [ H - Cursor home
 328:				; Esc J to Esc [ J - Clear to end of display
 329:				; Esc K to Esc [ K - Clear to end of line
 330:				; Esc Y <y> <x> to Esc [ <y> ; <x> H - Set cursor position
 331:				; Esc p to Esc [ 7 m - Reverse video on
 332:				; Esc q to Esc [ 27 m - Normal (positive) video
 333:				; Esc r to Esc [ 4 m - Underline on
 334:				; Esc u to Esc [ 24 m - Underline off
 335:				; Added 30/5/2025, initially to make the ZDE editor work properly:
 336:				; Esc L to Esc [ L - Insert line at cursor, pushing lines down
 337:				; Esc M to Esc [ M - Delete line at cursor, pulling lines up
 338:				; Esc E to Esc [ H Esc [ J - Home cursor and clear screen
 339:				; Esc d to Esc [ 1 J - Clear to start of display
 340:				; Esc e to Esc [ 25 h - Enable cursor
 341:				; Esc f to Esc [ 25 l - Disable cursor
